y&#34; } }, &#34;security&#34;: { &#34;#attributes&#34;: { &#34;userid&#34;: &#34;s-1-5-19&#34; } }, &#34;task&#34;: 0, &#34;timecreated&#34;: { &#34;#attributes&#34;: { &#34;systemtime&#34;: &#34;2023-03-27t14:44:43.415702z&#34; } }, &#34;version&#34;: 0 } } } the firewall rule&rsquo;s direction was set to &ldquo;2&rdquo; which means &ldquo;outbound&rdquo;. so, i think &ldquo;1&rdquo; means &ldquo;inbound&rdquo;? unable to find documentation regarding the integer values.
